RACE.RACE_TEXT: Bluebonnet S. LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR ACCREDITED TEXAS-BRED, FILLIES AND MARES, THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. No nomination fee. $375 to pass the entry box and an additional $375 to start. Supplemental nominations may be made at time of entry for $1,125 and shall include all fees. After payment of 1.5% of the purse to all owners finishing sixth through last, 60% of the remaining purse shall be paid to the winning owner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usual ti me of closing. Weights: Three Year Old, 118 lbs. Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of $25,000 in 2023 allowed 2 lbs.; Non-winners of $15,000 in 2023 allowed 4 lbs.; Non-winners of $10,000 since October 13, 2022 allowed 6 lbs. Maiden and claiming races not considered in allowances. Total earnings in 2022-2023 as determined by the information provided by Equibase Company, will be used in determining the order of preference. The field will be limited to fourteen starters. Horses not drawing a starting po
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMA DISCREET LADY prompt the pace from the outside of rivals, drifted a bit into the upper stretch and drew off to be well clear while being kept to pressure racing five to six wide. UPTOWNBLINGITHOME stalked the early going, moved up near the rail at the three eighths marker but was no match for the winner in the drive. UNIQUE BABE settled off the early going to race near the back of the pack early on, raced evenly late with no final run while racing. LADY AVE rated along early, made a five wide bid near the five sixteenths pole and flattened out in the drive. BOERNE set the early pace while racing near the three path, was through early and eased up on late. Official race time was hand timed.
